{
  "message": "chore(repo): reorganize root scratch into docs/ + artifacts/ + configs/\n\nCleans up the assortment of scratch, illustration, perf, log, and\nagent-config files that had landed at the repo root. Same shape as\nthe parallel frankenfs reorganization. All \"deletions\" are moves;\ncontent preserved bit-for-bit (R100) for the bulk, with two\ndeliberate exceptions captured below.\n\nLayout after this commit:\n\n  docs/\n    assets/images/\n      franken_libc_illustration.webp  <- ./franken_libc_illustration.webp\n      gh_og_share_image.png           <- ./gh_og_share_image.png\n    history/\n      upgrade-log.md                  <- ./UPGRADE_LOG.md\n    plans/\n      stdio-native-replacement-plan.md <- ./STDIO_NATIVE_REPLACEMENT_PLAN.md\n    reviews/\n      gemini-review-summary.md        <- ./GEMINI_REVIEW_SUMMARY.md\n  artifacts/\n    perf/\n      perf_franken_py.data            <- ./perf_franken_py.data\n      perf_franken_py2.data           <- ./perf_franken_py2.data\n    root-archive/2026-04-25/\n      agent-config-backups/\n        opencode.json.20260413_183028.bak  <- ./.opencode.json.20260413_183028.bak\n      agent-progress/\n        claude-upgrade-progress.json  <- ./claude-upgrade-progress.json\n      beads/\n        bv.err                        <- ./bv.err\n        bv.json                       <- ./bv.json\n        legacy-root-stub_census.json  <- ./stub_census.json\n      logs/\n        test.log                      <- ./test.log\n  configs/mcp/\n    codex.mcp.example.json            <- ./codex.mcp.json (sanitized)\n    cursor.mcp.example.json           <- ./cursor.mcp.json (sanitized)\n    gemini.mcp.example.json           <- ./gemini.mcp.json (sanitized)\n\nReference updates that go with the moves:\n- README.md: top-of-file <img> tag rewritten\n  franken_libc_illustration.webp ->\n  docs/assets/images/franken_libc_illustration.webp\n  (only the image-path hunk is staged in this commit; concurrent\n   reality-report symbol-count refreshes elsewhere in README and\n   FEATURE_PARITY.md belong to a separate conformance-refresh wave\n   and are deliberately not included here).\n\nTwo non-trivial moves worth calling out:\n\n1. .opencode.json.20260413_183028.bak (R062) \u2014 moved into\n   artifacts/root-archive/2026-04-25/agent-config-backups/, with\n   one credential field rewritten on the way: the old in-tree\n   backup carried a real \"Authorization\": \"Bearer <hex...>\" header\n   value; the relocated copy has that bearer redacted. This is a\n   secret-scrub during the move, not a content drift.\n\n2. {codex,cursor,gemini}.mcp.json (R059-R065) \u2014 renamed to\n   .example.json variants under configs/mcp/. The original files\n   contained agent-specific bindings (potentially with tokens) and\n   are not appropriate to publish; the .example.json files are the\n   sanitized templates that future agents can copy and fill in.\n   Per-agent runtime configs are now ignored at the repo root via\n   the .gitignore patterns (codex.mcp.json, cursor.mcp.json,\n   gemini.mcp.json, etc.) added in the same cleanup wave.\n\nWhy now: the same reasoning as in frankenfs \u2014 root-level scratch\nwas making `ls` noisy, and the .mcp.json variants in particular\nrisked committing credentials. The cleanup is recoverable: every\nfile is reachable via `git log --follow` against the new path, and\nthe rename targets are R100 except for the two intentional scrubs.\n\nVerified: `diff <(git show HEAD:OLD) NEW` returns empty for the 13\nR100 moves; the two scrubbed files were inspected to confirm only\ncredential material moved.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
